# Example for ~/.config/fish/conf.d/secrets.fish
#
# This file is NOT symlinked. To use:
#   cp ~/src/macbook-setup/fish/secrets.fish.example ~/.config/fish/conf.d/secrets.fish
#   # then add `set -gx VAR value` lines for each secret a tool needs.
#
# Each secret is documented by its consumer (e.g. an env var read by a
# Claude Code agent definition is described in that agent's file). When
# you copy this template, populate it with the secrets the tools you've
# installed actually need — there is no canonical list here on purpose.
